Sentencas: Electrical current flow is one of the important factors influencing high-temperature oxidation of SOFC interconnects.
Titulo: Effect of Electrical Current on Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Metallic Interconnect Oxidation in Syngas

Sentencas: To understand the effect of electric current on corrosion behavior, Crofer 22 APU and Haynes 230//SS430 clad coupons were exposed to a simulated coal syngas at 800 degrees C with a current density of 0.5 A/cm2, for 500 h. It was found that the scale formed on the positive side was thicker than that formed on the negative side.
Titulo: Effect of Electrical Current on Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Metallic Interconnect Oxidation in Syngas

Sentencas: In particular, for Crofer 22 APU, the morphology of the scale formed on the positive side was whisker-like while the scale formed on the negative side was predominantly cubic-shaped crystals.
Titulo: Effect of Electrical Current on Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Metallic Interconnect Oxidation in Syngas

Sentencas: For Haynes 230//SS430 clad sample, some grain-shaped crystals appeared on SS 430 (negative) side due to the breakaway oxidation.
Titulo: Effect of Electrical Current on Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Metallic Interconnect Oxidation in Syngas
